column5: Null cipher suites do not provide any data encryption and data integrity.
The SSL/TLS server accepts encryption  which does not require server authentication.
The TLS/SSL server supports export cipher suites intentionally crippled to conform to US export laws. Symmetric ciphers used in export cipher suites typically do not exceed 56 bits.
The server accepts very weak cipher algorithms. https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Old_backward_compatibility
The cipher key used for some cipher algorithms are too small (<128 bits).
The server accepts weak cipher algorithms. https://wiki.mozilla.org/Security/Server_Side_TLS#Intermediate_compatibility_.28default.29
